result.execSummary:
The defendant Nazareth Heinke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-THC (<=200 grams), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases 14CF382, 15CF74 and 15CM134 called together at 1:36pm [mo]
Defendant Nazareth Heinke in court, in custody with Attorney Samantha J. Humes.   ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.

As to Case 15CM134:
[Initial Appearance Occurs]
Service of Complaint admitted, reading waived, the charge and maximum penalties are recited. 
The Court orders that Mr. Heinke is to be booked on this case today.

As to Case 15CF74:
Mr. Heinke waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Trial.

Arraignment:
--service of Information admitted, reading waived

As to Case 14CF382, 15CF74 and 15CM134:
Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; pleas of "Guilty" entered on Case 14CF382 Count #1, Case 15CF74 Count #3 and Case 15CM134 Count #1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses all remaining counts of Cases 14CF382 and 15CF74.

Sentencing arguments given by ADA Hall
Sentencing arguments given by Attorney Humes 

On Case 14CF382 Count #1, Case 15CF74 Count #3 and Case 15CM134 Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 18 months, with conditions:

--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with any recommended treatment
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to be subject to random urinalysis (not less than once per month for first 3 months; thereafter per agent)
--to maintain employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--no possess or consume controlled substances without valid prescription
--no possession or consume of alcohol
--no possession of drug paraphernalia 
--no presence in bars, taverns, or liquor stores
--no contact with any known drug offender except for treatment purposes as deemed appropriate by the agent
--provide DNA sample to designee upon demand in case 14CF382 only 
--On Case 14CF382 Count #1 to pay costs of $268 plus the $250 DNA surcharge
--On Case 15CF74 Count #3 to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--On Case 15CM134 Count #1 to pay costs of $243  plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--On Case 14CF382 to pay drug testing fees in the amount of $50


As to Case 15CM134: The Court grants Mr. Heinke the opportunity to request expungement upon successful completion of Probation 
As to Case 15CM134: The Court does not require Mr. Heinke to register as a sex offender 

Sentence Credit:
---Case 14CF382: 42 days credit
---Case 15CF74: 43 days credit
---Case 15CM134: 0 days credit
